## Code rules

- Never hardcode secrets. Credentials live in `.env.local` (local) and Vercel env vars (production). Never commit `.env.local`.
- Never use the Vercel CLI. Pushes to `main` deploy automatically.
- Always work directly on `main` in `<!-- PARAMETERIZE: repo_local_path -->`. Never create branches or use `git worktree`. Worktrees create isolated copies the dev server can't see, breaking visual verification. Do not invoke worktree-creating tools (`EnterWorktree`, `Agent` with `isolation: "worktree"`).
- Do not push to GitHub unless the task explicitly says to commit and push. After every push, paste the commit URL (`<!-- PARAMETERIZE: github_repo_url -->/commit/<sha>`) and state "waiting for Vercel deploy." Do not declare the session task complete until <!-- PARAMETERIZE: visual_confirmer_name --> confirms the deploy reached production.
- Never preemptively pass `-c` config overrides to `git` without asking first.
<!-- OPTIONAL: stack_constraint_line -->
- Do not silently change <!-- PARAMETERIZE: critical_invariants -->. Document product-impacting changes in `docs/DECISIONS.md`.

